{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:43:54.620Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Health Mapping**\n\nI'm now focusing on mapping the backend's health status to the UI's health status. I've realized the backend provides more granular statuses (\"On Track\", \"Warning\", \"Critical\", \"At Risk\", \"Delayed\", \"Paused\") than the UI (\"On Track\", \"Warning\", \"Critical\"). I've created a helper function to map these, consolidating statuses where necessary, such as mapping \"Warning\", \"Paused\", and \"Delayed\" to \"Warning.\" I'm prioritizing accuracy in this health mapping. I'm moving onto the progress now.\n\nI'm now looking at phase-derived progress mapping! While the API doesn't have a direct `progress` field, I'm thinking I can derive it from the phase. For example, \"Phase I: Planning\" could reasonably translate to 15% progress.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
