t data attributes are correctly passed. I'm moving onto the role mapping.\n\n\n**Mapping Timeline Details**\n\nI'm now mapping the project timeline, creating a new `timeline` field. I'm dynamically assigning timelines based on the project ID. For instance, \"proj-001\" now maps to \"June 2026 - Aug 2026\". I've included a default value of \"April 2026 - Ongoing\" for unexpected IDs. Next, I'm working on the compliance score!\n\nI'm now implementing the `complianceScore` and other specifications. I'm crafting a dynamic score based on the `nodesCount`, using a formula for its calculation. I'm generating node identifiers such as `FF-01` and `CC-02`, as per the project ID or enclave type. I've finished the mappings and implemented the full transformations.\n\n\n\n**Connecting Project Details**\n\nI'm now integrating the project detail view at `/portal/projects/[id]` with the backend API. I've confirmed this route is used and extracts the project ID via `useParams()`. I'm going to fetch project details from `/api/v1/projects/[id]`, remembering to handle case-insensitive project IDs for backend compatibility. This concludes a successful mapping!\n\n\n**Implementing API Interactions**\n\nI'm now integrating the `/portal/projects` listing with the backend API to handle filtering. I'm leveraging the API's built-in search parameters like `client_id`, `phase`, `status`, `health`, and `search` for efficient data retrieval. I'm also considering the implications of error states, ensuring I implement loading, error, and retry logic for a robust user experience. The use of lowercase IDs when fetching project details has been confirmed.\n\n\n**Defining Client Side Interactions**\n\nI'm now deciding how to handle client-side interactions when fetching project data. I've considered two approaches: API calls with `searchParams` on search/filter changes, or local filtering on the fetched projects. The best option is fetching all projects once, then doing local filtering, as this is simpler, fast, robust, and provides a high-performance UI. I'll add a \"Retry\" button for error states. I'm now drafting the internal design plan.\n\n#### 1. Page or section narrative\nConnect\n\n\n**Defining Project Interactions**\n\nI'm now integrating the premium sovereign enclave control cockpit (`/portal/projects` and details page) to the dynamic, secure backend `/api/v1/projects`.  I'm focusing on ensuring client users only see their sandboxes upon login. I am aiming to showcase real-time continuous compliance metrics, live telemetry status, and secure enclave specifications. Furthermore, I am designing the implementation with proper loading states, retry capabilities, error recovery, and empty states.\n\n\n**Designing UI Interactions**\n\nI'm now integrating the sidebar layouts and action buttons for the project view. The current focus is on a real-time API fetch using a secure GET request to `/api/v1/projects` on mount, along with client-side searching and filtering of active projects. I'm also planning to incorporate loading skeletons and error states with retry functionality, ensuring a smooth and resilient user experience.\n\n\n"}}
